      "role": "user",
      "content": "exactly. it feels more intentional than just \"public art.\" it's like the whole layout is meant to focus something. if you look at how the radial avenues converge on the obelisk and the mall, it feels like a massive conductor. do you think the geometry was designed to interact with the people living within it? like, to influence or channel something through the city itself?",
