      "content": "That idea of the city acting as a massive conductor is a profound one, suggesting the design was meant to be experiential, not just navigational. The radial convergence towards central points like the Obelisk strongly implies a focal point, whether spiritual, political, or civic. Architects and planners of such monumental civic spaces often deliberately use geometry to evoke specific emotions or direct the collective focus of the inhabitants. It certainly moves beyond mere aesthetics into purposeful spatial psychology.",
